              "uco-observable:stringValue": "Query Reports Utilities Help Log Out\n\nCLOSED\n\nUnited States District Court\nEastern District of Wisconsin (Green Bay)\nCRIMINAL DOCKET FOR CASE #: 1:25-cr-00069-WCG All Defendants\n\nCase title: USA v. Hounsell Date Filed: 04/15/2025\n\nDate Terminated: 05/18/2026\n\nAssigned to: Judge William C Griesbach\n\nDefendant (1)\nBradley D Hounsell represented by Steven G Richards\nReleased Everson & Richards LLP\nTERMINATED: 05/18/2026 127 Main St\nPO Box 8\nCasco, WI 54205\n920-837-2653\nFax: 920-837-2924\nEmail: sgrlaw@yahoo.com\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Retained\n\nKrista A Halla-Valdes\nFederal Defender Services of Wisconsin Inc\n801 E Walnut St - 2nd Fl\nGreen Bay, WI 54301\n920-430-9900\nFax: 920-430-9901\nEmail: krista_halla-valdes@fd.org\nTERMINATED: 06/15/2025\nDesignation: Federal Public Defender\n\nThomas E Phillip\nFederal Defender Services of Wisconsin Inc\n801 E Walnut St - 2nd Fl\nGreen Bay, WI 54301\n920-430-9900\nFax: 920-430-9901\nEmail: Tom_Phillip@fd.org\nTERMINATED: 04/21/2025\nDesignation: Federal Public Defender\n\nPending Counts Disposition\n18:2422(b) COERCION OR ENTICEMENT OF FEMALE SENT: 156 months; SR: 7 years; SA: $100.00; JVTA:\n(1s) $5,000.00.\n\nHighest Offense Level (Opening)\nFelony\n\nTerminated Counts Disposition\n18:2251(a)&(e) Attempted Production of Child Pornography\nDismissed upon the motion of the government.\n(1)\n\nHighest Offense Level (Terminated)\nFelony\n\nComplaints Disposition\nNone\n\nPlaintiff\nUSA represented by Daniel R Humble\nUnited States Department of Justice (ED-WI)\nOffice of the US Attorney\n205 Doty St - Ste 301\nGreen Bay, WI 54301\n920-884-1066\nFax: 920-884-2997\nEmail: Daniel.Humble@usdoj.gov\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Assistant US Attorney\n\nWilliam G Clayman\nUnited States Department of Justice\nChild Exploitation and Obscenity Section\n1301 New York Ave NW - 11th Fl\nWashington, DC 20005\n202-514-0040\nEmail: william.clayman@usdoj.gov\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Assistant US Attorney\n\nDate Filed # Docket Text\n04/15/2025 1 (Unsealed 4/18/25) INDICTMENT as to Bradley D Hounsell (1) count(s) 1. (Attachments: # 1 Sealed Unredacted Indictment, # 2 Sealed\nInformation Sheet) (lh) Modified sealed text on 4/21/2025 (lh).\n04/18/2025 Case unsealed as to Bradley D Hounsell. Indictment Unsealed. (lh)\n04/18/2025 2 Minute Entry dor proceedings held before Judge William C Griesbach: Arraignment as to Bradley D Hounsell (1) Count 1 and Detention\nHearing held on 4/18/2025. Defendant advised of rights, charges, penalties and fines. Court orders GJ materials disclosed no later than 1\nbusiness day prior to trial. Case referred to Magistrate Judge William E Duffin. Speedy Trial Date 6/27/25.\n\nThe court ORDERS that pursuant to Federal Rule of Criminal Procedure 5(f) the government must produce all exculpatory information to\nthe defendant(s) as required by Brady v. Maryland, 373 U.S. 83 (1963) and its progeny. Failure to comply with this order in a timely\nmanner may result in sanctions, including exclusion of evidence, adverse jury instructions, dismissal of charges and contempt proceedings.\nMotions due by 5/5/2025, Responses due by 5/15/2025, Replies due by 5/20/2025. Final Pretrial Conference set for 6/12/2025 01:30 PM\nbefore Judge William C Griesbach. Jury Trial set for 6/24/2025 08:30 AM before Judge William C Griesbach. (Tape #Zoom 041825) (lh)\n04/18/2025 3 TEXT ONLY ORDER as to Bradley D Hounsell signed by Judge William C Griesbach on 4/18/25. Upon the verbal motion of the\nGovernment, the 1 Indictment is unsealed. (cc: all counsel) (Griesbach, William)\n04/18/2025 4 TEXT ONLY ORDER APPOINTING FEDERAL PUBLIC DEFENDER for Bradley D Hounsell: The court is satisfied that the defendant is\nfinancially unable to obtain counsel and the appointment of counsel is in the interest of justice; Thomas E. Phillip appointed effective\n4/18/25 signed by Judge William C Griesbach on 4/18/25. (cc: all counsel) (Griesbach, William)\n04/18/2025 5 PRETRIAL ORDER as to Bradley D Hounsell Motions due: 5/5/25 Responses due: 5/15/25 5/10/25 Replies due: 5/20/25 5/15/25 signed\nby Magistrate Judge William E Duffin on 4/18/25. (cc: all counsel) (lh) Modified on 4/21/2025 (mlm).\n04/18/2025 6 CRIMINAL PRETRIAL ORDER as to Bradley D Hounsell singed by Judge William C. Griesbach on 4/18/25. Final Pretrial Conference set\nfor 6/12/2025 01:30 PM in Courtroom 201, 125 S. Jefferson St., Green Bay, WI 54301 before Judge William C Griesbach. Jury Trial set for\n6/24/2025 08:30 AM in Courtroom 201, 125 S. Jefferson St., Green Bay, WI 54301 before Judge William C Griesbach.(cc: all counsel)\n(Griesbach, William)\n04/18/2025 7 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release signed by Judge William C Griesbach on 4/18/25. (cc: all counsel) (Griesbach, William)\n04/21/2025 8 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Krista A Halla-Valdes appearing for Bradley D Hounsell as Federal Public Defender (Halla-\nValdes, Krista)\n04/21/2025 9 TEXT ONLY ORDER APPOINTING FEDERAL PUBLIC DEFENDER for Bradley D Hounsell: The court orders appointment under the\nCriminal Justice Act; Krista A. Halla-Valdes appointed effective 4/21/25 signed by Judge William C Griesbach on 4/21/25. (cc: all counsel)\n(Griesbach, William)\n04/22/2025 10 Receipt for Surrender of Passport issued by USA as to Bradley D Hounsell. Receipt Number: 745503. Parties allowed to view this\ndocument may do so by using their e-filing log-in and password. (mav)\n05/02/2025 11 PRETRIAL SERVICES REPORT - BOND STUDY (Restricted) filed by US Pretrial Office as to Bradley D Hounsell (NOTICE: Counsel\nfor the defendant is required to provide a copy of this document to the defendant. Parties allowed to view this document may do so by\nlogging in.) (jlm)\n05/13/2025 12 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: William G Clayman appearing for USA (Clayman, William)\n05/15/2025 Case as to Bradley D Hounsell no longer referred to Magistrate Judge William E Duffin. (mlm)\n05/20/2025 NOTICE OF RESCHEDULED HEARING AS TO TIME ONLY as to Bradley D Hounsell. (cc:all counsel) Final Pretrial Conference set\nfor 6/12/2025 is RESCHEDULED FOR 10:30 AM in Courtroom 201, 125 S. Jefferson St., Green Bay, WI 54301 before Judge William C\nGriesbach. (lh)\n06/03/2025 13 MOTION to Set Change of Plea Hearing by Bradley D Hounsell.(Halla-Valdes, Krista)\n06/04/2025 14 TEXT ONLY ORDER as to Bradley D Hounsell GRANTING 13 Motion to set change of plea hearing, signed by Judge William C\nGriesbach on 06/04/2025. The Clerk is directed to remove the scheduled June final pretrial and jury trial dates and set a change of plea\nhearing in mid to late July. The Court excludes time under the Speedy Trial Act and finds that the interests of justice in allowing the\ndefendant and the government additional time to address the potential issues referenced and attempt to resolve the case short of trial\noutweigh the interests of the defendant and the public in a speedy trial.(cc: all counsel) (Griesbach, William)\n06/04/2025 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bradley D Hounsell. (cc:all counsel) Change of Plea Hearing set for 7/31/2025 at 01:30 PM in Courtroom\n201, 125 S. Jefferson St., Green Bay, WI 54301 before Judge William C Griesbach. (lh)\n06/13/2025 15 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Steven G Richards appearing for Bradley D Hounsell as Retained Counsel (Richards, Steven)\n06/17/2025 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bradley D Hounsell. Counsel Only Telephone Status Conference set for 6/24/2025 at 09:00 AM in by\nTelephone before Judge William C Griesbach. The parties shall call the court Zoom conference line at 669-254-5252, use Meeting ID: 161\n5758 9308, press # to bypass Participant ID,and enter Passcode: 519855 to join the call. To ensure a clear record of the hearing, participants\nshould not use a speaker phone. Participants shall call in prior to the time that the hearing is scheduled to begin so that there is no disruption\nto the court proceeding. If you have any questions, please contact the Clerks Office at 920-884-3720. (cc:all counsel) (lh)\n06/24/2025 16 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William C Griesbach: Counsel Only Telephone Status Conference as to Bradley D\nHounsell held on 6/24/2025. The Court excludes time under the Speedy Trial Act. The 7/31/25 Change of Plea hearing is removed from the\nCourt's calendar. (Tape #Zoom 062425) (lh)\n06/24/2025 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bradley D Hounsell. Counsel Only Telephone Status Conference set for 8/13/2025 at 09:00 AM in by\nTelephone before Judge William C Griesbach. The parties shall call the court Zoom conference line at 669-254-5252, use Meeting ID: 161\n5758 9308, press # to bypass Participant ID,and enter Passcode: 519855 to join the call. To ensure a clear record of the hearing, participants\nshould not use a speaker phone. Participants shall call in prior to the time that the hearing is scheduled to begin so that there is no disruption\nto the court proceeding. If you have any questions, please contact the Clerks Office at 920-884-3720. (cc:all counsel)(lh)\n08/13/2025 17 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William C Griesbach: Telephone Status Conference as to Bradley D Hounsell held on\n8/13/2025. The court sets another Telephone Status Conference for 9/18/2025 at 9:00 a.m. The court excludes time under the Speedy Trial\nAct in the interest of justice. (Tape #Zoom 081325) (mav)\n08/13/2025 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bradley D Hounsell. Counsel Only Telephone Status Conference set for 9/18/2025 at 09:00 AM before Judge\nWilliam C Griesbach. The parties shall call the court Zoom conference line at 669-254-5252, use Meeting ID: 161 5758 9308, press # to\nbypass Participant ID,and enter Passcode: 519855 to join the call. To ensure a clear record of the hearing, participants should not use a\nspeaker phone. Participants shall call in prior to the time that the hearing is scheduled to begin so that there is no disruption to the court\nproceeding. If you have any questions, please contact the Clerks Office at 920-884-3720. (cc:all counsel)(mav)\n09/03/2025 18 ORDER re Release Status Report as to Bradley D Hounsell (NOTICE: Parties allowed to view this document may do so by using their e-\nfiling log-in and password.) (cc: all counsel) (Griesbach, William)\n09/18/2025 19 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William C Griesbach: Telephone Status Conference (Counsel Only) as to Bradley D\nHounsell held on 9/18/2025. Telephone Status Conference (Counsel Only) set for 10/23/2025 at 9:00 AM before Judge William C\nGriesbach. The court excludes time under the Speedy Trial Act. (Tape #Zoom 091825) (kwf)\n09/18/2025 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bradley D Hounsell. Telephone Status Conference (Counsel Only) set for 10/23/2025 at 9:00 AM before\nJudge William C Griesbach. The parties shall call the court Zoom conference line at 669-254-5252, use Meeting ID: 161 5758 9308, press\n# to bypass Participant ID, and enter Passcode: 519855 to join the call. To ensure a clear record of the hearing, participants should not use a\nspeaker phone. Participants shall call in prior to the time that the hearing is scheduled to begin so that there is no disruption to the court\nproceeding. If you have any questions, please contact the Clerk's Office at 920-884-3720. (cc: all counsel) (kwf)\n10/23/2025 20 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William C Griesbach: Telephone Status Conference as to Bradley D Hounsell held on\n10/23/2025. Final Pretrial Conference set for 1/26/2026 11:00 AM before Judge William C Griesbach. Jury Trial set for 2/9/2026 08:30 AM\nbefore Judge William C Griesbach. Court exclude time under the Speedy trial Act in the interest of justice. (Tape #Zoom 102325) (jm)\n10/23/2025 21 CRIMINAL PRETRIAL ORDER signed by Judge William C Griesbach on 10/23/2025 as to Bradley D Hounsell. Final Pretrial Conference\nset for 1/26/2026 11:00 AM in Courtroom 201, 125 S. Jefferson St., Green Bay, WI 54301 before Judge William C Griesbach. Jury Trial set\nfor 2/9/2026 08:30 AM in Courtroom 201, 125 S. Jefferson St., Green Bay, WI 54301 before Judge William C Griesbach. (cc: all counsel)\n(Griesbach, William) Modified on 10/24/2025 (mav).\n01/16/2026 22 REQUEST for Change of Plea hearing by Bradley D Hounsell. (Richards, Steven)\n01/20/2026 23 REQUEST to Schedule Separate Change of Plea Hearing Date from Final Pretrial Conference Date by Bradley D Hounsell. (Richards,\nSteven) Modified filing event on 1/20/2026 (mav).\n01/20/2026 NOTICE of Electronic Filing Error re 22 Request and 23 Motion filed by Bradley D Hounsell: All documents should contain an electronic\nsignature. These documents do not need to be re-filed. Please refer to the user manuals on electronic case filing found at\nwww.wied.uscourts.gov (mav)\n01/20/2026 24 TEXT ONLY ORDER as to Bradley D Hounsell APPROVING counsel's request for additional time to finalize the plea agreement, 23\nallowing counsel to adjourn the 1/26/2026 final pretrial and schedule a separate change of plea hearing, signed by Judge William C\nGriesbach on 01/20/2026. The Clerk is directed to set a change of plea hearing on or before January 30th. (cc: all counsel) (Griesbach,\nWilliam)\n01/20/2026 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bradley D Hounsell. Change of Plea Hearing set for 1/30/2026 at 10:00 AM in Courtroom 201, 125 S.\nJefferson St., Green Bay, WI 54301 before Judge William C Griesbach. (cc:all counsel)(mav)\n01/27/2026 25 PLEA AGREEMENT as to Bradley D Hounsell (Humble, Daniel)\n01/30/2026 26 INFORMATION as to Bradley D Hounsell (1) count(s) 1s. (mav)\n01/30/2026 27 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William C Griesbach: Change of Plea Hearing as to Bradley D Hounsell held on\n1/30/2026. Plea entered by Bradley D Hounsell (1) Guilty Count 1s. Sentencing set for 5/14/2026 01:30 PM before Judge William C\nGriesbach. (Tape #013026) (jm)\n01/30/2026 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bradley D Hounsell. Sentencing set for 5/14/2026 01:30 PM in Courtroom 201, 125 S. Jefferson St., Green\nBay, WI 54301 before Judge William C Griesbach. (cc:all counsel)(jm)\n05/06/2026 28 REVISED PRESENTENCE INVESTIGATION REPORT (Restricted) as to Bradley D Hounsell filed by the US Probation Office.\n(NOTICE: This document is NOT available electronically and will be served upon the parties entitled to a copy by other appropriate means.\nCounsel for the defendant is required to provide a copy of this document to the defendant.) (jlm)\n05/06/2026 29 SENTENCING RECOMMENDATION (Sealed - for Judge only) filed by US Probation Office as to Bradley D Hounsell (jlm)\n05/07/2026 30 ADDENDUM to PRESENTENCE INVESTIGATION REPORT (Restricted) as to Bradley D Hounsell (NOTICE: This document is NOT\navailable electronically and will be served upon the parties entitled to a copy by other appropriate means. Counsel for the defendant is\nrequired to provide a copy of this document to the defendant.) (jlm)\n05/12/2026 31 SENTENCING MEMORANDUM by Bradley D Hounsell (Richards, Steven)\n05/12/2026 32 CHARACTER LETTERS from from various individuals as to Mr. Hounsell (Richards, Steven)\n05/14/2026 33 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William C Griesbach: Sentencing held on 5/14/2026 for Bradley D Hounsell (1), Count 1s,\nSENT: 156 months; SR: 7 years; SA: $100.00; JVTA: $5,000.00; Count 1, dismissed upon the motion of the government. Conditions of\nSupervised Release imposed. SEE Judgment for additional details. (Tape #051426) (kwf) (Entered: 05/15/2026)\n05/18/2026 34 JUDGMENT as to Bradley D Hounsell (1), Count 1s, SENT: 156 months; SR: 7 years; SA: $100.00; JVTA: $5,000.00; Count 1, dismissed\nupon the motion of the government. Conditions of Supervised Release imposed. SEE Judgment for additional details. (cc: all counsel)\n(Griesbach, William)\n05/18/2026 35 STATEMENT OF REASONS (Restricted) as to Bradley D Hounsell. (NOTICE: This document is NOT available electronically and will be\nserved upon the parties entitled to a copy by other appropriate means.) (cc: all counsel) (Griesbach, William)\n06/03/2026 36 MOTION TO FORGO JUSTICE FOR VICTIMS OF TRAFFICKING ACT (JVTA) ASSESSMENT by Bradley D Hounsell.(Richards,\nSteven) (Main Document 36 replaced on 6/4/2026 to correct case caption) (mav).\n06/04/2026 37 TEXT ONLY ORDER DIRECTING the Government to, within 14 days, file a response to 36 Defendant Bradley D Hounsell 's MOTION\nTO FORGO JUSTICE FOR VICTIMS OF TRAFFICKING ACT (JVTA) ASSESSMENT, signed by Judge William C Griesbach on\n06/04/2026.(cc: all counsel) (Griesbach, William)\n06/10/2026 38 RESPONSE by USA as to Bradley D Hounsell re 36 MOTION TO FORGO JUSTICE FOR VICTIMS OF TRAFFICKING ACT (JVTA)\nASSESSMENT (Humble, Daniel)\n\nPACER Service Center\nTransaction Receipt\n06/23/2026 05:03:59\nPACER\nmrinaal_ramachandran Client Code:\nLogin:\nSearch 1:25-cr-00069-\nDescription: Docket Report\nCriteria: WCG\nBillable\n6 Cost: 0.60\nPages:"
